{td}Data-driven planting and management decisions based on historical environmental trends{/td}
{td}Retention period must be specified - per peer review R2, 90-day minimum is recommended to cover a full growing cycle. Acceptance criteria: operator can select date ranges, view line charts for all monitored parameters, and data is retained for at least 90 days. Linked to GMS-43, GMS-44 (export). Trend visualization format (chart type, granularity) should be defined in SRS.{/td}
{td}{status:PROPOSED|color=Yellow}{/td}
{td}Analyzed: operator/owner planning decisions, action is viewing historical trends, circumstance is seasonal planning and performance review, outcome is improved data-driven decisions. 90-day retention requirement logged per peer review R2. Moving to Proposed.{/td}
