{tr}
{td}SHR-24{/td}
{td}{jira:GMS-49}{/td}
{td}Job Story{/td}
{td}Greenhouse Operator / Business Owner{/td}
{td}Should Have{/td}
{td}Review historical environmental trend data presented as visualizations, selectable by date range, covering previous growing months{/td}
{td}When planning the next growing season, analyzing correlations between past environmental conditions and crop performance, or preparing evidence-backed recommendations for yield optimization{/td}
{td}Operator makes data-driven planting and management decisions informed by actual historical environmental performance rather than memory or guesswork{/td}
{td}This is the Job Story counterpart to GMS-42 (SHR-23 — already Proposed). Per peer review R2 (WP4.2), a 90-day minimum data retention period is required to cover a full growing cycle and provide meaningful seasonal trend analysis — this was formally acknowledged and logged for the SRS architecture phase. Acceptance criteria: operator can select custom date ranges; line charts available for all monitored parameters (soil moisture, temperature, humidity, CO2, light intensity); data retained for a minimum of 90 days. Trend visualization format — chart type, data granularity (hourly vs daily aggregation) — to be defined in SRS. This requirement feeds directly into the report export capability (GMS-43/50) and the ROI savings comparison (GMS-56). Cross-references: GMS-42 (User Story pair, SHR-23), GMS-43/50 (export reports), GMS-56 (ROI savings — depends on this data being stored){/td}
{td}{status:PROPOSED|color=Yellow}{/td}
{td}Requirement analyzed and refined. Decomposed into: User = greenhouse operator/business owner, Action = review historical environmental trends via charts and date-range selection, Circumstances = seasonal planning and crop performance review, Outcome = improved data-driven management and planting decisions. Classified as Should Have — complements real-time monitoring for longer-term decisions but does not block core pilot functionality. 90-day minimum data retention confirmed per peer review R2 and logged for SRS data architecture definition. Acceptance: date-range selection; line charts for all parameters; 90-day retention minimum. Visualization format (granularity, chart types) deferred to SRS. Linked to GMS-42 (US pair, SHR-23). Moving to Proposed.{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}SHR-25{/td}
{td}{jira:GMS-43}{/td}
{td}User Story{/td}
{td}Business Owner / Greenhouse Investor{/td}
{td}Should Have{/td}
