{td}When meeting with investors, agronomists, or regulatory authorities and needing documented evidence of system performance or raw data for analysis{/td}
{td}Operator can export data in structured formats (Excel/CSV) and/or formatted summaries suitable for external sharing{/td}
{td}GMS-44 ('export sensor data to a spreadsheet') has been consolidated into this requirement and marked INVALID, as both requirements share the same user, circumstance, and outcome. This requirement now covers both export modes: (1) raw sensor data export — Excel/CSV with minimum fields: timestamp, sensor ID, parameter name, value, unit (per peer review R5 and explicit survey requests); (2) formatted summary report suitable for investor/agronomist presentation. Acceptance criteria to be defined in SRS covering both output types.{/td}
{td}{status:PROPOSED|color=Yellow}{/td}
{td}Consolidated with GMS-44 (marked INVALID — duplicate). Updated scope to cover both raw CSV/Excel export and formatted report generation. R5 export field spec (timestamp + sensor ID + unit) now formally included in this requirement. Moving to Proposed.{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}SHR-26{/td}
{td}{jira:GMS-50}{/td}
{td}Job Story{/td}
{td}Business Owner / Greenhouse Operator{/td}
{td}Should Have{/td}
{td}Export a formatted summary report of system performance data from the dashboard for external professional sharing{/td}
{td}When meeting with investors, agronomists, or regulatory authorities and needing documented, structured evidence of greenhouse environmental performance{/td}
{td}Operator can present a professional, readable summary of system performance; investor confidence is strengthened and agronomist advisory quality is improved{/td}
{td}This is the Job Story counterpart to GMS-43 (SHR-25 — already Proposed). Important scope note: GMS-44 (SHR-49) was marked INVALID and its scope absorbed into GMS-43, which now covers both formatted summary reports AND raw CSV/Excel export. This ticket (GMS-50) should be reviewed at team discussion to confirm it does not duplicate GMS-43 after that consolidation. If it does, it should be marked INVALID. If a distinct scope remains — specifically the formatted investor-facing presentation report as opposed to raw data export — that distinction must be clearly defined and documented. Minimum export fields per peer review R5: timestamp, sensor ID, parameter name, value, unit. Formatted output format (PDF or structured document) to be defined in SRS. Dependency: historical data module (GMS-42/49) must be in place before reports can be generated. Cross-references: GMS-43 (User Story pair, SHR-25), GMS-49/42 (historical data dependency), GMS-56 (ROI data dependency).{/td}
{td}{status:PROPOSED|color=Yellow}{/td}
{td}Requirement analyzed and refined. Decomposed into: User = business owner/investor, Action = export formatted performance summary report, Circumstances = investor or agronomist meeting requiring documented system performance evidence, Outcome = professional evidence suitable for external sharing. SCOPE NOTE: GMS-44 (SHR-49) was marked INVALID and absorbed into GMS-43, which now covers both export modes. Team must confirm at review whether this ticket retains unique scope (formatted investor-facing report vs raw data) or should also be marked INVALID. Minimum fields per peer review R5: timestamp, sensor ID, parameter name, value, unit. Report output format to be defined in SRS. Dependency on historical data module (GMS-42/49). Linked to GMS-43 (US pair, SHR-25). Moving to Proposed pending team scope review.{/td}
