{tr}
{td}SHR-27{/td}
{td}{jira:GMS-53}{/td}
{td}User Story{/td}
{td}Small-scale Farmer{/td}
{td}Must Have{/td}
{td}Provide a GMS solution priced within the budget constraints of small-scale farmers{/td}
{td}When a small farmer is evaluating whether to invest in greenhouse automation for the first time{/td}
{td}Farmer can adopt the GMS without prohibitive upfront cost; the primary user segment is not excluded by price{/td}
{td}50% of survey respondents are small-scale farmers — affordability is a prerequisite for adoption, not a nice-to-have. Project Charter budget estimate: 800–2,000 EUR for hardware. This requirement covers the adoption barrier; demonstrating ROI through savings is handled separately by GMS-54 (Should Have). Peer review R1 noted the cost savings measurement needs a defined mechanism — logged for SRS acceptance criteria phase. Linked to GMS-55 (Job Story pair).{/td}
{td}{status:PROPOSED|color=Yellow}{/td}
{td}Requirement analyzed and refined. Decomposed into: User = small-scale farmer, Action = provide affordable solution, Circumstances = pre-adoption evaluation with limited budget, Outcome = adoption without significant financial risk. Scope clarified: this requirement covers the entry cost barrier only; ROI demonstration is a separate Should Have (GMS-54/56). Peer review R1 finding logged — cost savings measurement mechanism to be defined in SRS acceptance criteria. Hardware budget reference: 800–2,000 EUR per Project Charter. Linked to GMS-55. Moving to Proposed.{/td}
{/tr}
