{td}SHR-50{/td}
{td}{jira:GMS-51}{/td}
{td}Job Story{/td}
{td}Business Owner / Greenhouse Operator{/td}
{td}Should Have{/td}
{td}Export raw sensor data to Excel or CSV format from the dashboard for compliance record-keeping or external analysis{/td}
{td}When preparing compliance records, advisory meeting materials, or sharing sensor data with agronomists, investors, or regulatory authorities{/td}
{td}Sensor data is available in a structured, interoperable spreadsheet format that external professionals and regulatory bodies can directly use{/td}
{td}IMPORTANT — overlap risk with GMS-43 (SHR-25) and GMS-50 (SHR-26). GMS-44 (SHR-49) was already marked INVALID as a duplicate of GMS-43. This ticket (GMS-51) covers the same core outcome (CSV/Excel export) already absorbed into GMS-43. Team must evaluate at the review session: if GMS-43 already fully covers raw CSV/Excel export with the minimum field specification (timestamp, sensor ID, parameter name, value, unit — per peer review R5), then this ticket should also be marked INVALID. If a distinct scope exists — specifically the compliance and regulatory use case as a separately documented output with regulatory-specific fields — that distinction must be explicitly defined to justify keeping this open. Multiple survey respondents and the expert (Bragarenco mentioned Excel export) confirmed this format is needed. Cross-references: GMS-43 (SHR-25), GMS-50 (SHR-26), GMS-44/SHR-49 (INVALID — absorbed).{/td}
